  %h2 Call for participation

  %p
    To increase collaboration between industry and academia in the field of
    networking, the
    %a{ :href => "https://irtf.org/" } Internet Research Task Force (IRTF)
    and the
    %a{ :href => "https://www.internetsociety.org/" } Internet Society (ISOC)
    in cooperation with
    %a{ :href => "http://www.sigcomm.org/" } ACM SIGCOMM
    are organizing a workshop on Research and Applications of Internet
    Measurements (RAIM), scheduled for the Saturday in between the
    %a{ :href => "http://conferences2.sigcomm.org/imc/2015/" } 2015 ACM SIGCOMM Internet Measurement Conference (IMC)
    in Tokyo and the
    %a{ :href => "https://www.ietf.org/meeting/94/" } 94th Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF) meeting
    in Yokohama.

  %p
    This workshop will bring together researchers and
    practitioners that are advancing the state of the art in measuring networked
    systems to share measurement-based insights into operational networks, to
    improve the use of research in protocol design decisions, and to suggest
    relevant new topics for research.

  %p
    %em Attendees requiring an invitation letter for a visa:

    If you are attending ACM IMC, the ACM will generate one for you as part of
    their registration process. Otherwise, you can
    %a{ :href => "https://ietf.org/meeting/register.html" } register for the IETF meeting
    and have the IETF system generate a letter for you afterwards. You do
    %strong not
    need to pay the registration fee to have the letter generated, and you do
    not need to pay the IETF registration fee to attend the RAIM workshop.

